WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.290 --> 00:00:03.510
Everyone wants to know how
accurate their forecasts are.

00:00:03.510 --> 00:00:06.090
Does your forecasting
method give good forecasts?

00:00:06.090 --> 00:00:07.820
Are they better than
other methods out there?

00:00:07.820 --> 00:00:11.340
There are many ways of measuring
the accuracy of forecasts and

00:00:11.340 --> 00:00:14.790
the answers to these questions
depends on what is being forecasted,

00:00:14.790 --> 00:00:19.150
what accuracy measure is being used,
and what type of data set you have.

00:00:19.150 --> 00:00:21.540
We'll take a look next at
which forecasting errors and

00:00:21.540 --> 00:00:25.550
accuracy measurements we can use to
judge what a good forecasting model is.

